\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces DDI Severity Recalibration Framework. DrugBank DDI descriptions are matched with DDInter severity labels to create a validated dataset (n=37,164). A 70/30 stratified split separates training (n=26,014) and test (n=11,150) sets. Keyword weights are derived from training data using log-likelihood ratios. Aggregate scores are classified using percentile thresholds to produce the target severity distribution. Validation against DDInter test set yields 66.4\% exact accuracy. Detailed algorithms in Supplementary S1.}}{2}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:flowchart}{{1}{2}}
